cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper proposes a novel paradigm for learning with streaming data where the feature space can evolve unpredictably. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data science (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on learning and prediction, we believe that cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.CV, and cs.SI.
